Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery rosette bowl; pale brown clay with silver mica; interior black with added red band lined in white; exterior: reserved with two bands on lower wall; dot decoration (part of a rosette) to left; black lines at break to right; double axe graffito cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.453)
